TY  - JOUR
T1  - Probabilities as Similarity-Weighted Frequencies
AU  - Billot, Antoine
AU  - Gilboa, Itzhak
AU  - Samet, Dov
AU  - Schmeidler, David
Y1  - 2005/07/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/07/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2005.00611.x
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1125
EP  - 1136
VL  - 73
IS  - 4
KW  - Probability
KW  - similarity
KW  - case-based reasoning
KW  - relative frequencies
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2005.00611.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - A decision maker is asked to express her beliefs by assigning probabilities to certain possible states. We focus on the relationship between her database and her beliefs. We show that if beliefs given a union of two databases are a convex combination of beliefs given each of the databases, the belief formation process follows a simple formula: beliefs are a similarity-weighted average of the beliefs induced by each past case.
ER  - 

